{"isHeader":true,"content":"Flapjack Topping"},{"content":"Place butter in mixing bowl and melt <b>3 min\/80°C\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add flour, oats, sugar and golden syrup then mix <b>20 sec\/\/speed 3<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then mix again <b>20 sec\/\/speed 3<b>. Finish mixing by hand with spatula then scatter over apples in dish. Bake for 35-40 minutes (180°C) until top is golden brown and crunchy. Meanwhile, clean mixing bowl then, 15 minutes before the end of baking time, remove ice cream from freezer."},{"content":"Once crumble is ready, cut ice cream into cubes (4 cm). Place cubes in mixing bowl and beat <b>30 sec\/speed 6<b> then, with aid of spatula, churn <b>30 sec\/speed 4<b>."},{"content":"Serve crumble hot with scoops of cinnamon ice cream."}],"basicInfo":["medium","15m","9h","8 pieces"]}